originalText.text: Horrible. The employee tried to tell me that my reservation was for tomorrow. That was incorrect, so I showed it to him again pointing out that he was wrong. Then he took my key and I asked for a second to grab my bags. After taking my items out he tells me that he can't take me car and that I need to leave. I was beyond confused. I asked for a refund and he said I would need to cancel it myself and get a refund myself. I  can't believe that how bizzar of an experience this was. Wasted my money and time. Ended up parking on the street and getting a ticket. Good thing I was able to communicate with my bank and got my refund.

originalText.text: I made a reservation through Parkwhiz.  They took my money.  I parked in the correct lot.  I got a parking ticket for nonpayment - expired. I sent Parkwhiz the parking pass and the ticket.  Their answer is they aren’t responsible and I have to deal directly with the vendor.  They literally have all the information but won’t even make a call on behalf of their customer.  I’ve done thousands of dollars of business with Parkwhiz over the years. Never again. Shortsighted business practices kill a business.  I deleted the app from my phone and will share with anyone who will listen.  Absolutely GROSS.

originalText.text: These people have changed.  No integrity.  While it is messed up that they accept a booking for a garage that is full and get denied access.  They always made good on it quickly and refunded the charge.  Well that has changed, they initially responded to my issue and even asked for receipt of garage I ultimately had to use...assuming they would refund the money collected (service not rendered) and make up difference with a credit.  Well after that and several follow up emails, no response.  So ultimately, they STOLE $16 from me...and I ended up paying $56 total to park when I had booked a spot from them for $16.  Disappointing, I was a loyal user for a long time BECAUSE of their integrity

originalText.text: Offer hourly parking passes for garages that NEVER ACCEPT VEHICLES WITHOUT A MONTHLY PARKING PASS! This caused me extreme inconvenience after arriving at my reserved garage and then the garage telling me they only accept monthly parkers. ParkWhiz should know that! Huge waste of money, time and energy. Very irresponsible on the part of ParkWhiz. Won't use them again and will not recommend them. Recommend you stick with using SpotHero as I've never had this problem with SpotHero.  If you try to call ParkWhiz, you just reach an answering machine. No one ever calls back after you leave a voicemail message, so their customer service also is poor.

originalText.text:
I've been using Park Whiz for years, especially the last one, as my partner was a transplant and cancer patient at the hospital. Needless to say, I have spend a small fortune in parking, each time using park whiz. Numerous times per week, some reservations costing upwards of 50.00; that adds up. Last week, we had an oncology appointment. The garage address was 219 East 31st. At that approximate address, there was a sign which said "park," and an arrow pointing down, at a WALL. After driving around the block a few times, and looking for the correct address amidst numerous garages, I saw scaffolding and a hidden driveway next to a garage labeled 214 East 31st; my reservation was for 219. I parked, and missed the appointment with my significant other. A completely hidden garage, and the wrong address.
Park Whiz did not give me a refund. They kept saying "Thanks for your feedback!" I mean, the. money I've spent with them makes me SICK. Creeps.
I have switched over to Spot Hero.
